How to reset TM2
1. Power OFF
2. Power ON while holding PRGRM CONVRS
3. Enter M 6000000 60FFFFF
4. Press Write/Enter
5. Press Reset when SUCCESS displayed
6. Restart Machine
7. Enable E-STOP
8. Turn Setting 7 off (parameter lock)
9. Press Alarm
10. Enter DEBUG
11. Press Write/Enter
12. Go to Setting 26 (serial)
13. Enter Serial Number (1074420)
14. Press Write/Enter
15. Insert Flash Drive
16. Press LIST PROG
17. Press Right Arrow to highlight USB
18. Press F4
19. Highlight "Load All - Reconfigure" (may be slightly different phrase)
20. Enter name of files to load without extension (ex: TM2-2017)
21. Press Write/Enter
22. Press Current Commands
23. Press Page Down to show time / date
24. Enter date in this format: "01-17-2017"
25. Press Write/Enter
26. Enter time in this format: "17:29" (insert : by pressing SHIFT+9)
27. Press Write/Enter

REF: Page 30 of 2011 Haas Electrical Service Manualâ€‹
